e the student body has the diversity required for today's workplace, where students graduate from rigorous programs in a multitude of disciplines, and where a strong work ethic is part of the students' makeup. You can find all of these qualities here on our campus. According to the ranking of National Universities by U.S. News and World Report, UIC's 30,000 students represent the most racially and ethnically diverse pool of students in the Midwest. UIC confers more than 5,000 bachelor, graduate, and professional degrees each year from fifteen academic colleges and professional schools including Business Administration, Engineering, and Liberal Arts & Sciences. More than 70% of our students gain valuable experience by working during their years at UIC.       Post A Position      To find out how to post full-time, part-time, and internship jobs and more you can follow the instructions on our “Post A Position” page. If you already know how to, you can use the link below to head over to our careers website using the second link below.    How to Create A Post    UICcareers         Career Fairs      Learn about the 5-10 career and job fairs hosted by UIC Career Services and Student Employment throughout the year. Most are restricted to UIC student and UIC Alumni; however, several are also open to the public    Upcoming Fairs         On-Campus Interviews      To assist you in your recruiting activities, we use the UICcareers site to schedule on-campus interviews, to maintain a database of student resumes, and to communicate with students. Employers may post job openings, schedule on-campus recruiting, and pre-select all of their candidates for campus interviews at the UIC careers site.    Learn More    UICcareers         Information Tables & Sessions      UIC Career Services provides a variety of ways to reach our students to promote your opportunities, as well as to increase knowledge of your organization to our students.  An information session provides a more formal setting to promote your organization and your employment opportunities. Employers use information tables to promote employment opportunities in a highly visible area located in our student center.    Learn More         Employer Partner Program      Becoming a member of the UIC Career Services Employer Partners Program provides you with additional services and visibility options to reach students and alumni while also helping us continue to enhance and extend our resources and services. The annual membership supports your program-building and key initiatives such as marketing to UIC students and branding your organization on campus — efforts that ensure you a highly qualified pool of prospective employees and interns.    Learn More         Additional Outreach & Student Engagement      UIC Career Services provides a variety of ways to reach our students to promote your opportunities, as well as to increase knowledge of the organization itself to students.  In addition to Career Fairs, Information Sessions, and Information Tables, additional student engagement opportunities include industry panels, site visits, and targeted outreach.     Learn More         Directions / Hotels      The UIC Office of Career Services is located in the UIC Student Services Building, Room 3050, located at 1200 West Harrison Street. We are accessible by public transportation and there is parking nearby.    Driving & Public Transportation Options    Hotel Options            Employers    Back to main content           Post A Position    UICcareers    Career Fair Information for Employers    On-Campus Interviews    Information Tables & Sessions    Employer Partner Program    Additional Outreach & Student Engagement Opportunities    Directions / Hotels                  UIC Logo        Career Services         Students    Career Planning Guide    Make an Appointment    FAQs      Employers    Post a Position    UICcareers.com      Campus Partners    Campus Partners    Program/Workshop Request Forms   